  "texts": [
    "Similarly, the temperature of decomposition of Bi 2 F e 4 O 9 has been observed to vary between 934 • C and 961 • C [21], while the peritectic decomposition of BiF eO 3 is cited in a wide range, from 852 • C to 934 • C [23].Further complicating matters, Palai et al. [21] proposed a decomposition pathway for BiF eO 3 [25], (e) Lu et al.",
    "[20], (f) Morozov et al. [22] are indicated along with our observations (g) in red.originating from the γ phase, a hypothesis that has been questioned by Lu et al.",
    "[20], due to the perceived thermodynamic instability of the γ phase.To understand these discrepancies, we constructed the phase diagram in Figure 1 by compiling data from previous work [18][19][20][21][22][23][24] and refining it with our own observations, marked (g) in red.",
    "These identify the emergence of a liquid phase at 835 • C for the 70: 30 precursor mixture.",
    "This melting behaviour of the bismuth-rich material, which is different from the peritectic decomposition of the stoichiometric BiF eO 3 at ∼920 • C (observed further to the right of the diagram), provides a clearer delineation of phase boundaries and improves understanding of this complex system."
  ]
